==Swedish==
===Noun===
'''hor'''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPAchar|/huːr/}}
#(''archaic'') [[adultery]], [[fornication]]: ''begå hor'' "commit adultery"
#:''Hon fick tjugo rapp på torget för att hon begått '''hor'''.''
#:"She received twenty lashes in the public square for committing adultery."

====Etymology====
From Old Swedish ''hor'' with the same meaning. Related to [[whore]].

